'''Bid Barzeh-ye Sefidar''' ({{lang-fa|<U+0628><U+064A><U+062F><U+0628><U+0631><U+0632><U+0647> <U+0633><U+0641><U+064A><U+062F><U+0627><U+0631>}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''B<U+012B>d Barzeh-e Sef<U+012B>d<U+0101>r'''; also known as '''B<U+012B>d Barzeh''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3755011|Bid Barzeh-ye Sefidar}}</ref> is a village in [[Sepidar Rural District]], in the [[Central District (Boyer-Ahmad County)|Central District]] of [[Boyer-Ahmad County]], [[Kohgiluyeh and Boyer-Ahmad Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 100, in 20 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|17}}</ref>  

